  "title": "You Have Got Pizza",
  "version": "1.1.0",
  "summary": "Portable PRG32 arcade cartridge about making pizza in an academic piazza.",
  "description": "You Have Got Pizza is an original PRG32 arcade game for the European RISC-V Summit 2026 demonstration track. The player is a professor collecting dough, sauce, cheese, and basil while avoiding hungry students. This build packages the C version as a portable ABI-table cartridge by default so it can be built, uploaded, and published through the same workflow used by DeviceDemo.",
